sentences: Jamell Maurice Demons (born May 1, 1999), known professionally as YNW Melly (backronym for Young Nigga World Melly), is an American rapper and singer.
In November 2019, he released his debut album, Melly vs. Melvin, peaking number eight on the Billboard 200.
In February 2019, he was arrested and charged with two counts of first-degree murder and faces life imprisonment or the death penalty if convicted.
He is also a suspect in the 2017 murder of a sheriff's deputy in Gifford.
In March 2019, Demons pleaded not guilty to the double-murder charges and is currently awaiting trial.
